No ostentatious frame, but rather the quality of the area reserved for the bed, so the mattress and base give a real basis for a good bed.
They must of course complement each other harmoniously to please a concrete user.
During the choice several things are decisive: the weight, the height, the age, the state of health as well as the sex of the owner.
The type of interior in which the mattress and base are placed is also important.
A typical example?
For example, in the country house where latex mattresses are not continuously sleeping are not appropriate because they "warm up" slowly.
In addition, they have a higher weight than standard polyurethane mattresses.
They need to be returned frequently.
If they do not also have enough ventilation channels in the heart, and if they also remain on a solid board, they retain moisture. Mould can also form there.
The habit is also decisive in the choice.
Anyone who spends the clearest time abroad where very thick mattresses are frequently used with a softening layer, will hardly feel well on a low and hard surface.
"That's how all the hobeyists coming back from NHL complain they can't sleep there".
"For their tired shoulders, feet and ribs, they needed mattresses with a softening layer of lazy foam".
