"Today everything works well, Tempur, the Italian Magnifex but also the Czech Tropico have suitable mattresses for example.
You don't need to be a NHL guy to be able to enjoy a lazy foam.
This "miracle" just works.
It optimizes its rigidity and shape depending on the heat absorbed or adapts to the heat of your body.
Nothing puts pressure on you and you won't turn around in the night like after a tough game.
You're just sleeping better.
The lazy foam also works as a protection against the esquarres.
For the choice of mattress depending on your size, add the length of the feet, about 21/34 cm.
A man and a woman of a size of 180cm therefore need a bed of 210/220cm.
The minimum width for each for a two-seater bed should be 90 cm or a total of 180 cm.
For single beds, for example, singles, it is recommended to take at least 120 /140 cm.
It's convenient in case of a visit.
'However it is a simple rule for the width of the bed: when you are lying on the back you should lay hands comfortably with the elbows slightly folded. Helena Prokopova, President of the Association of Mattress-Buttermakers and decorators who has been dedicated for several years to the problem of healthy sleep and ergonomics of furniture and teaches it in specialized schools.
For a two-seater bed each needs its own bed base and mattress, so be careful however during the shopping to choose the height of the mattress well.
Otherwise you will only have to climb the base at different heights and this is not feasible on all bed frames.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, spring mattresses at least 15 cm, of which count for the layer of shape and ventilation at least three centimeters.
"In the touch or sitting on the mattress you should not feel the springs," warns Hélena Prokopova.
Each mattress requires a well-defined type of base.
The bed-spring, when the mattress and the bed-spring are united like Siamoese sisters, has nothing to do in the bedrooms.
The mattresses were very bad; it should not be washed, which is commonly done today.
And since during the night one normally sweats from 0.2 to 0.75 l of sweat it is clear that after 5/7 years, the mattress begins to recall a large (and clogged) sieve.
For this purpose, specialists refuse to make a claim over a 25-year lifetime for a mattress or a lifetime warranty.
But it's all hers.
And for this an experienced advice from the sellers: for a mattress of 120/140cm, give up, for the coating of the mattress, hygiene or washing but instead add a protective mattress that you can easily remove and wash.
And even if nowadays it is common to manufacture coatings with zipper for the whole set, that is to say that after opening we have two parts (for washing and the size of the washing machine is very important!) otherwise handling for the big models (and for one person only) becomes when we remove them a fight between a light weight and a heavy weight on a ring.
Do you have a rigid board in your bed instead of a bed base?
Never!
Maximum for a bed for visitors for one night only.
However, equip the board (if there are none) with ventilation holes and use the spring mattress with a minimum height of 15cm with sachet springs (from Germany Taschenfederken) and an aeration layer.
A polyurethane mattress shall not be part of a bed of this type.
For single-positioned slats with 14/18 slats, latex or sandwich mattresses (perhaps the combination of latex and coconut), are ideal but it will always be better for you to have a mattress with more slats, 28 and above, where the slats are doubled in the lower part of the kidneys and thus it is possible to regulate the rigidity of the slats.
For multi-position mattresses, spring mattresses should not be taken because they do not respond to changes in position.
Next to the adjustment of the rigidity of the slats one can also install what is called a shoulder cradle.
This is a special connection of the slats that allows to press or even tilt the slat so that the shoulder of the sleeper "integrates" well.
For men who have "shoulders as wide as their backs," this is really an important thing.
This thing is already being considered by mattress manufacturers who for "masculine" have begun to use a softening area at the shoulder level.
But they also think of women - they again offer them a softer surface at the hips.
