The era of lazy or viscoelastic foams with an open cell structure and a large thickness was started with Tempur matter at a "cosmical" rhythm.
This began as a matter for NASA because astronauts were undergoing huge load factors at the start.
The Tempur softens with heat and hardens, on the contrary, with cold.
It adapts perfectly to the hot human body and distributes an optimal pressure.
For this it is ideal against sleeping sickness and for an increase in comfort during sleep.
Viscoelastic foams are used not only for mattresses but also for health products, such as special cushions for feet that relieves legs and the venous system.
Czech manufacturers use e.g. EucathermC or Twinsaver foam or of the same type.
Devices to track people are increasingly required by parents who want to look after their children.
Fear for their child causes more and more people to think about watching them through a GPS.
The system, set up at the beginning to search for cars can just as well be used to trace the movement of people and help in some cases as for example that of the little Anicka Janatkova.
The instrument is currently as big as a matchbox but will soon be the size of a watch.
The case of little Anicka moved a large number of people and they began to look for ways to better protect their children.
Even if the price is to disrupt their privacy.
"We are trying to tell everyone that this is not espionage but only another way to reduce the likelihood of another tragedy," says Petr Pilin of MAcro Weil, one of the suppliers of tracing devices on the Czech market.
"I confess that there may be cases of misuse of such devices, such as putting it in the bag of a person who is not aware, but I have not yet encountered such cases".
"The majority of people are customers who actually buy the product for security reasons," adds Pilin.
According to him, children should always know for what purpose "the box" is used and how to use it in an emergency.
The children's psychologist, Dana Bockova, draws attention to the fact that if the child does not want to focus on him something of this type, he will get rid of it.
'And even the smaller ones can show great creativity when it comes to getting rid of something on purpose when they don't want to be under control'.
"Mobile phones, which can be cut off like these tracking devices, have already led parents to long expectations," says Bockova.
According to her, the fact that this type of device can help in the event of an attack is very questionable.
"If this is a prepared abduction, the author will do everything he can to ensure that the child does not have an electronic device that can locate him".
"Currently, it's the phone".
"As soon as tracing devices develop, they (the criminals) will also seek them out because the sale will be supported by an advertising campaign".
"In such cases criminals will always be ahead of the police," says the psychologist.
She admits, however, that such devices can help in an assault not prepared by a paedophile.
According to Robert Cech of RC Monitoring, which offers tracing services for both cars and people, it says that having this type of device can help, even if it is destroyed in the case of an assault.
"The device may be configured in such a way that it is in regular emission after a specified period of time".
"If the device is destroyed, it remains the last position of the person concerned".
"The more expensive devices also have a tiltometer that immediately signals the position of the person who slipped and ends up lying down without moving," says Cech.
According to him the so-called smart mobile phones that are equipped with a navigation system, can offer a comparable service after formatting it with a special pretext.
The problem with current tracking systems is that it is either a device similar to those worn in pendants the size of a match box or the smallest telephone devices.
We can always lose them.
According to Pilina of Macro Weil, this is why tests are currently being conducted to make devices that resemble common digital watches.
"This will have the advantage that the potential attacker will not be able to recognize the tracing device".
"Or he'll find out after a while, which will give the police a little more time," he adds.
Whether the tracking device is developed in the form of a bracelet or pendant, it will always use the same technology as for tracing cars.
This is a combination of GPS position acquisition systems (which is commonly used in auto-nautization) and a mobile phone function that alerts the current position of a vehicle.
