Until now, I have benefited from the contacts I have obtained through the competitions.
The franchise sale of his hotel helped Lukas Pytloun to win the Best Individual Entrepreneur competition.
The winner of last year's Best Individual Entrepreneur competition was 28-year-old entrepreneur Lukas Pytloun.
His adventure to success is like in a movie.
Lukas Pytloun liked to travel.
And abroad, he realized that in Libérec there was a lack of a quality hosting site at a reasonable price.
From his savings on what he had earned while working abroad and with the help of a bank loan he bought a small building of 5 apartments half demolished.
Knowing that he was still studying in the trossème year of higher education, it was a courageous action.
"The relationship between quality and price of accommodation in our area made me want to do something," says Lucas Pytloun.
He began to rent the first apartment rebuilt to foreign workers.
He reinvested the profit in the building that he turned into a boarding house with 54 beds.
Since then, his entrepreneurial activity has enabled him to open in Libérec 4 pensions, two restaurants of style and two hotels with a total capacity of nearly 300 beds of all categories of accommodation.
The most comfortable of them was until recently the four-star Pytloun design hotel.
This year another of the same quality came to him.
"We just signed a contract with a hotel in Ostrova U Tise where we sold our franchise concept and other Pytloun hotel franchise candidates showed up," the number one entrepreneur last year.
"And for the sale of the license for the operation of a large-scale hotel the winner at the Entrepreneur of the Year competition served well," adds Pytloun with gratitude.
The victory brought him more popularity and to be known in Liberec and its surroundings.
"People recognized me in the streets, congratulated me often and, I must say, it was very pleasant," he recalls.
It recommends participation in this competition to all those who are trying to do something.
It is not necessary to win but any opportunity to be visible is good.
He says he's still using his contacts and knowledge that he couldn't have obtained in any other way.
"With those I met through the contest I began to maintain trade relations regularly.
According to him, fame related to success also had an impact on employees.
And he's got about 70.
"I especially observe in them the loyalty and pride of having engaged in something that has been generally recognized".
"This is not, and by far, the only result of my personal work, but the result of a good work of all of us together.
"Only my name is pushed forward," says Lucas Pytloun modestly.
I wish my successor a better year than we had in Farmet.
The euphoria of victory was quickly replaced by the effects of the crisis.
Thanks to the sense of the goal of the winner Farmet has the worst moments behind him.
The one who came to collect the prize in Slovakiansky dum for the first place in the competition for the Firm of the Year organized by Vodaphone last year is Karel Zdarsky the owner of the Farmet company.
The jury rewarded the efforts with which it transformed a tool shop in Ceska Skalice into a firm with a turnover of 100 million crowns.
'I can say that the award not only encouraged my colleagues and increased our self-confidence to fight competition,' said the winner of last year's competition today.
At the beginning of the history of the Farmet company there was a desire to do something useful.
And so when the state proposed to Karel Zdrasky's father to rent the small workshop as compensation after the confiscation of property by the communists, he did not hesitate long, refused a career in a firm where he worked at the time, and created a company with a few comrades in his father's entourage for the manufacture of plastic bathtubs.
Not very long after they began to specialize in vegetable oil presses.
After 18 years it has become the largest automatic press manufacturer in Central Europe.
The company was known even in the non-specialized public after the successful completion of the competition through the media.
"Not only did our customers really get to know the Farmet brand better but also the foreign partners who started to realize that they were collaborating with a company that got the greatest success in its country of origin," says Karel Zdarsky.
But last year did not happen at Farmet only in the euphoria of victory.
The company's valuation was based on the economic results for 2008 and in part for 2009.
And precisely in 2009 it was the most difficult year for the sale of engineering machines.
At the height of the crisis, which did not really affect citizens, companies were forced to stop their investment projects and start limiting their purchases of new materials and technologies.
"We obviously did not escape this situation".
"The turnover fell by 40 percent, and we had to limit our production and even lay off," explains Karel Zdarsky.
A viable society must be aware that from time to time unpopular measures must be taken.
But they managed the situation correctly and retained beneficial results even though they were inferior to those they had before the crisis.
However, in Farmet, they continued uncompromisingly to invest in research and development.
"We have built with the endowments a training and research center, strengthened the company's presentation in international exhibitions-exhibitions and won the main awards in national exhibitions," says Zdarsky.
Everything leaves us to think that the crisis is behind them.
The numbers of cases go up and with them the number of employees also.
"To the new winner I wish this pleasant feeling of victory but in a calm atmosphere," says Karel Zdarsky.
The investigation that suppresses senseless regulations.
The Absurdity of the Year investigation is for the fourth time a part of the business clan.
Some absurd regulations could be removed.
The little glorious winner of this year's investigation into the absurdity of the year was the obligation to bring to the offices documents that officials can obtain online.
More than one third of the 4,000 voters voted for this.
For example, the social affairs authorities asked for a paper extract from the business register, while the official can obtain it in two clicks.
It changes because of the investigation.
"The Czech Social Insurance Administration will no longer ask for the extract from the Trade Register for control of insurance payments," said Jana Buranova, spokesperson for the Czech Social Insurance Administration (CSSZ).
Bringing out all the regulations and decrees that companies and entrepreneurs have to fill in in the Czech Republic and removing those that are absurd is the meaning of this year's absurdity contest.
This survey is again this year for the fourth time part of the business clan organized by Hospodarske noviny and has even greater popularity.
Last year, 3000 voters came forward, and at least 4000 this year brought their votes.
And it's no wonder, there are in our country the most various legal obligations that only slow down the company, and, this, more and more.
"We may be the number of documents to fill out for tax returns at the top places in the world," says Karel Havilik of the Association of Small and Medium Enterprises and Entrepreneurs of the Czech Republic.
Simplification of entrepreneurial activity has become a stated goal of all governments in recent years.
Compared with the world, the situation in the Czech Republic is not improving at all.
According to the World Bank, the Czech Republic is in 74th place in terms of conditions for the company, an increase of 8 places compared to last year.
The "Absurdity of the Year" competition was first launched in 2006 and continues each year under the same scenario.
Anyone can report administrative and bureaucratic absurdities every year from April to the end of September, the final deadline before the competition closes.
To report there is the website www.firmaroku.cz. Then, the organizer of the contest selects seven candidates for "the anti-price" and lets the public vote during the month of October on the website www.firmaroku.cz/absurdita and on www.ihned.cz.
The Absurdity that received the largest number of votes is declared the winner.
Until last year's last investigation, it was a hundred, or more exactly 105 regulations and decrees that lost their sense of existence.
Comments are sent by entrepreneurs but also professional unions and teachers.
Among the "finalists" of the competition, therefore among the nominees is for example the obligation that maintenance vehicles for motorways and expressways pay tolls, or that contractors with twenty employees, repaint two offices and two toilets every two years.
The list of seven proposals is published on the competition website.
The proclamation of the contest, which always begins in early November at Wenceslas Square in Prague, is part of a happening in which political and public figures regularly participate.
