'Economic prosperity cannot work when the state puts astonishment in the legs of entrepreneurs and for this my objective is to delete, each year, at least three dozen paragraphs which today only complicate the business', said Martin Kocourek, the Minister of Industry and Trade.
The effort to remove absurd decrets is not a sword stroke in the water.
In 2007, what did not appeal to people was the requirement for contractors to report three days before at the office for the individual business at the location of the business, the intention to go to an exhibition or pilgrimage with a stand.
This obligation was removed with the addition of the Single Business Act.
The second most widely accepted requirement in 2007, which was to report to the Labour Office a 30-day tour of duty for a foreign employee, was removed with the so-called Green Card Act.
