If the court summoned her, she said, she would refuse to go.
"Cambodia is at peace and stable," she said.
"If there's more prosecution, there'll be war."
Prime Minister Hun Sen, who defected the Khmer Rouge in 1978, has also repeatedly warned that instability would occur if the court sued several suspects; although experts and historians dispute this.
