Faced with European resistance, in Germany we are beginning to speculate on the three possible exits from the crisis.
The first, a strong euro, integrated by itself, Austria and Holland, among other countries, and the south would abandon the monetary zone.
The second, the recovery of the Mark, even though now it seems of science fiction, with a very favorable current of opinion, almost a 50% of the population.
The third, a new conception of the euro, in line with the German proposals for greater macro-economic control, fiscal rigour, fines to the countries that transgress them, possible suspensions of payments by one of them and extension to the private sector of the costs of potential adjustments.
