2013 will mean the creation of a new monetary zone, in which countries that break the rules will be severely punished, they may be forced to declare themselves in cessation of payments and, in this case, the private sector will also bear a share of the costs.
Germany warns us that we must follow a severe path of growth with high rates of savings and investment, moderation in consumption, improvements in productivity and competitiveness and positive external balances.
